================================================================================
PART C — ACCEPTABLE USE (Voice Safety)
================================================================================

The synthetic-voice capabilities of this software carry a heightened risk of
abuse. As a binding condition of the licenses granted in Part A, you agree NOT
to use the software, in whole or in part, to:

  * Impersonate any person or organization without their explicit consent.
  * Commit fraud, identity theft, or any deceptive practice.
  * Clone, synthesize, or reproduce any individual's voice without that
    individual's informed and verifiable consent (or other lawful basis).
  * Produce deceptive synthetic media intended to mislead as to authenticity.
  * Harass, threaten, defame, or harm any person.
  * Generate content that is unlawful in the jurisdiction where it is created,
    distributed, or consumed.

Violation of Part C is a violation of this License and triggers the Termination
clause in Part A. The full, governing statement of these obligations is set out
in VOICE_USAGE_POLICY.md, which is incorporated into this License by reference.


